  sil = SilhouetteVisualizer(kmeanModel, is_fitted=False, ax=ax.flatten()[index])
  sil.fit(df_minmaxs)
  sil.finalize()
  print(f"For k={K}, the average silhouette score is {sil.silhouette_score_}")

insight:
  "Although K=2 and K=3 yield the highest silhouette scores, these configurations produce overly coarse clusters that lack business interpretability.
  Based on the elbow point around K=5 or 6 and stable silhouette scores within this range, we selected K=6 as the optimal balance between cluster quality and actionable segmentation".


